variance in HUI2 scores. Parameter estimates of all SF-36 components showed 
statistical significance at the P < 0.05 level.
CONCLUSIONS: Results of this study provide a quantitative link between two 
important measures of health status. The present model can be used to estimate 
health utility summary scores in studies that have collected SF-36 data.

